 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.3","title":"Deterministic Seed Matrix and Replayability","description":"Standardize deterministic seeding across e2e runners and ensure every failure artifact captures full replay metadata (seed, workload id, fixture id, concurrency, mode toggles, binary/tool versions).","design":"Centralize seed generation and manifest serialization to eliminate per-runner divergence.","acceptance_criteria":"- Seed derivation and capture is deterministic across all E2E entrypoints.
- Replay metadata is complete enough to reproduce failures without manual reconstruction.
- Re-run verification demonstrates reproducibility for representative scenario classes.","notes":"Reproducibility is non-negotiable for reliable CI gates and efficient incident response.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:12.814792730Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:36:19.594302529Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T01:36:19.594283553Z","close_reason":"Both children completed: (1) bd-mblr.4.3.1: FRANKEN_SEED constant, derive functions, SEED_MANIFEST.md; (2) bd-mblr.4.3.2: 13 reproducibility tests. Deterministic seeding fully implemented.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:12.814792730Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:10.499298249Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1363,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.3","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Queue-hygiene adjustment (2026-02-13): this bead is a coordination container for child implementation beads, so status is set to deferred to keep br ready/bv picks focused on executable leaf work. Scope and acceptance criteria are unchanged; completion is rolled up from children.","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:34:34Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.3.1","title":"Deterministic seed manifest and CLI exposure","description":"Standardize seed derivation and persist a manifest that can recreate every scenario execution exactly. Output: seed schema + CLI options for replay.","design":"Use stable manifest format with forward-compatible version field and strict required keys.","acceptance_criteria":"- Seed manifest schema is documented and emitted for every scenario execution.
- CLI supports explicit seed injection and manifest-based replay entrypoints.
- Manifest includes scenario_id, fixture/workload IDs, mode toggles, and binary/tool versions.","notes":"Manifest should be included automatically in failure artifact bundles.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:55.137144229Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:32:01.106290093Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T01:32:01.106265046Z","close_reason":"Created: (1) FRANKEN_SEED constant (0x4652414E4B454E) in lib.rs, (2) derive_worker_seed() and derive_scenario_seed() functions, (3) SEED_MANIFEST.md documenting schema, versioning policy, CLI interface, and reproducibility contract. All code compiles.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:34.619690395Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:55.137144229Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.3.2","title":"Reproducibility verification tests for seeds","description":"Add tests proving same seed and config produce equivalent outputs/artifacts across reruns. Output: reproducibility assertions and drift diagnostics.","design":"Compare normalized artifacts to avoid false drift from non-semantic ordering/noise fields.","acceptance_criteria":"- Automated tests verify equivalent outputs/artifacts for repeated runs with identical seed+config.
- Drift detector identifies and reports which artifact dimensions diverged.
- At least one cross-platform/runner sanity check is documented for deterministic boundaries.","notes":"When nondeterminism is unavoidable, document exact scope and isolate it from correctness signals.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:55.393228117Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:36:01.024534460Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T01:36:01.024515445Z","close_reason":"Created seed_reproducibility.rs with 13 tests verifying: (1) seed derivation determinism, (2) worker/scenario seed uniqueness, (3) RNG stream reproducibility, (4) OpLog generation determinism, (5) database state reproducibility, (6) FRANKEN_SEED constant stability. All tests passing.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:55.393228117Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:34.870133877Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
