 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","title":"Failure artifact bundle schema and collector","description":"Define artifact bundle schema (logs, seed, workload, DB snapshots/diffs, environment metadata) and implement collector integration. Output: one-bundle-per-failure triage package.","design":"Treat bundle writer as reusable library component with schema validation and versioning support.","acceptance_criteria":"- Artifact schema includes logs, seed manifest, workload inputs, expected/actual diffs, and environment metadata.
- Collector integration writes one deterministic bundle per failure with scenario_id/run_id indexing.
- Collector is validated by tests that intentionally trigger failures and inspect bundle completeness.","notes":"Schema should align with unified logging fields; alignment is validated by downstream log-quality gates (bd-mblr.5.4.1) so artifact-bundle implementation can proceed in parallel with schema refinement.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:55.648991504Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:58.167647577Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:58.167615507Z","close_reason":"Created failure_bundle.rs with: (1) FailureBundleManifest schema v1.0, (2) ScenarioInfo, ReproducibilityInfo, EnvironmentInfo, FailureInfo types, (3) FailureType enum (Assertion, Panic, Divergence, SsiConflict, etc.), (4) FailureBundleBuilder with fluent API, (5) Convenience functions bundle_assertion_failure and bundle_divergence_failure, (6) 4 unit tests. All tests passing.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:35.127327962Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:35.383497319Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:35.638929346Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:55.648991504Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.5","title":"Complete E2E script-suite coverage and execution manifest","description":"Create an authoritative map and runner strategy for every e2e integration script so the suite is complete, deterministic, and auditable. Scope: inventory all e2e/*.sh and equivalent integration entrypoints, map each to canonical scenario IDs, identify blind spots, and define one reproducible execution manifest covering required environment, ordering, and expected artifacts.","design":"Treat script-suite coverage as a data product: maintain machine-readable manifest + traceability matrix consumed by CI and triage tooling.","acceptance_criteria":"- Authoritative inventory includes every E2E script entrypoint with deterministic invocation contract and scenario coverage mapping.
- Execution manifest defines canonical ordering/sharding rules, required environment, and artifact expectations.
- Any uncovered scenario is explicitly flagged with rationale and linked remediation task.","notes":"This track complements scenario implementation by guaranteeing script-level executability and auditability of the full E2E surface.","status":"deferred","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:28:54.704231383Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:34:34.708187573Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:28:54.704231383Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1364,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Queue-hygiene adjustment (2026-02-13): this bead is a coordination container for child implementation beads, so status is set to deferred to keep br ready/bv picks focused on executable leaf work. Scope and acceptance criteria are unchanged; completion is rolled up from children.","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:34:34Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","title":"E2E script inventory and scenario traceability matrix","description":"Build a complete machine-readable matrix: script path, invocation contract, scenario IDs covered, storage mode, concurrency mode, failure artifact paths, and logging schema version. Acceptance: no uncataloged e2e integration script remains; each scenario has explicit script linkage or an intentional gap annotation with rationale.","design":"Generate baseline inventory automatically, then curate explicit overrides for ambiguous mappings to minimize drift.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Matrix includes every e2e script/entrypoint with scenario IDs, invocation contract, storage/concurrency modes, deterministic seed source, required artifacts, and log schema version. 2. Every canonical P0/P1 scenario is mapped to at least one script or linked to an explicit gap issue. 3. Output is machine-readable and diff-friendly for CI drift checks.","notes":"Primary traceability key is scenario_id; this matrix must stay aligned with bd-mblr.4.1.2.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:00.232621941Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T04:59:49.430386021Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T04:59:49.430366835Z","close_reason":"Complete: 81 scripts inventoried, 106 scenario IDs, 9 gap annotations, 15 unit tests, E2E script, structured JSON logging","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:00.232621941Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:00.232621941Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:00.232621941Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1431,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Evidence: 15 unit tests passing, E2E script (scripts/verify_e2e_traceability.sh --json), 81 scripts cataloged on disk, 106 unique scenario IDs, 9 gap annotations. Module hash: ef89c29e5f902772c9892fb8f89459d340230333be08ae229a0a9715f78740c3. Reproduction: cargo test -p fsqlite-harness --lib -- e2e_traceability && bash scripts/verify_e2e_traceability.sh --json","created_at":"2026-02-13T04:59:44Z"}]}
