 {"id":"bd-mblr.5.5.2","title":"Retrofit all e2e scripts to unified detailed logging schema","description":"Update each e2e integration script to emit structured, schema-compliant logs at key lifecycle boundaries (start, setup, execute, validate, artifact bundle, terminal status). Acceptance: no script emits ad-hoc-only terminal messages; all script outputs include traceable event records with artifact pointers and failure context.","design":"Migrate by script family with reusable logging helpers and contract checks to avoid one-off formatting divergence.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Every e2e script emits schema-compliant structured events for lifecycle boundaries: start, setup, execute, validate, artifact-bundle, terminal. 2. Required traceability fields (trace/run/scenario/seed/outcome/duration/error/artifact refs) are always present. 3. No required script remains ad-hoc-terminal-output-only for diagnostics.","notes":"Retrofit sequencing depends on inventory + unified schema migration so script outputs remain interoperable with existing tooling.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:27.569786055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:47:08.251957791Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:46:39.815805148Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:27.569786055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:27.569786055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:27.569786055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:27.569786055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1353,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Dependency rationale: bd-mblr.4.4.1 is now a prerequisite so script-level logging emits artifact references that conform to the canonical failure bundle schema.","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:47:08Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","title":"Automated conformance test: per-script logging completeness and quality","description":"Add an automated checker that executes representative script runs and validates logging completeness, field-level schema conformance, and diagnostic sufficiency (actionable root-cause context on failures). Acceptance: CI fails when scripts omit required fields, lose trace continuity, or produce non-actionable terminal failures without artifact linkage.","design":"Run representative script executions through validator pipeline and assert both syntactic and semantic logging quality rules.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Automated conformance checker validates per-script schema compliance, trace continuity, and actionable failure context quality. 2. Checker fails CI for missing required fields, broken trace joins, or missing artifact linkage. 3. Emits machine-readable + human-readable conformance report artifacts for triage.","notes":"This final gate depends on script retrofit (bd-mblr.5.5.2), missing-script completion (bd-mblr.4.5.3), and shared log-quality tests (bd-mblr.5.4.1). Redundant direct blockers are removed where transitive dependencies already guarantee sequencing.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:33.981518469Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:16.140921385Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:16.140879888Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:42:12.953263995Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:42:22.502522818Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:15.601226906Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:15.874783422Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:33.981518469Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1354,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Dependency rationale: added direct edge to bd-mblr.5.5.1 to make schema-profile ownership explicit for conformance validation, even though transitive dependency existed through bd-mblr.5.5.2.","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:47:08Z"},{"id":1358,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Restored explicit dependencies on schema profile (bd-mblr.5.5.1) and full-suite orchestrator (bd-mblr.4.5.2) so conformance checks validate both field contract and canonical execution surface.","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:31:29Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.6","title":"Comprehensive Unit Test Expansion and Failure Diagnostics","description":"Define and implement granular, high-signal unit tests across core crates so behavior invariants are validated with deterministic, reproducible diagnostics and minimal mock reliance.","design":"Use a crate-by-crate invariant matrix and deterministic fixtures so unit tests provide root-cause evidence, not opaque failures.","acceptance_criteria":"Every core crate has explicit invariant-focused unit-test coverage targets; new unit suites are deterministic and reproducible; failures emit rich context sufficient for triage without rerunning under a debugger.","notes":"Deferred intentionally for queue hygiene: this bead is a container/coordination umbrella, not a direct implementation lane. Work proceeds through its child tasks; reopen/close this bead during milestone rollup and completion review.","status":"deferred","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:01:08.395933046Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:51:03.695814243Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.6","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:01:08.395933046Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.6","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:02:48.792192376Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
